<subSubSection id="0A6223C32F3A61ED4DEE6E2182D9A540" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FE125FFAE9522C4090D84EEDFF0E20B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="EF7BE2A4C41F4743C9D23289B24098B8" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina pallidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">Boletina pallidula</taxonomicName>
Edwards, 1925: 573 (
<bibRefCitation id="F9C9DA2C7A00C07CB32512A3EB8C2765" author="Edwards, F. W." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="505 - 670" title="British fungus-gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). With a revised generic classiﬁcation of the family." volume="1925" year="1925">Edwards 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8D9F016F5CC342777B839F891C76C1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="1AB29BD8136D248EB2C4027728E4F9A8" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina subnitidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnitidula">Boletina subnitidula</taxonomicName>
Sasakawa, 1994: 298 (
<bibRefCitation id="6FBDD70477C781FFFFCC8A6A043F0B7B" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
), syn. n.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FE253E903CAE5E7522EF4DE15D4D4580" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="2ECD3C767754F650F16DCEF59E4D1F16" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A81BD3489FAF7EA08E1E90C245D1D47" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">
<taxonomicName id="2CFBE4FE3090CFF95CF1A19A5462B5E4" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina pallidula" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">Boletina pallidula</taxonomicName>
was described by Edwards (
<bibRefCitation id="CE4DD9CC40CAF69036AAA668FB689386" author="Edwards, F. W." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="505 - 670" title="British fungus-gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). With a revised generic classiﬁcation of the family." volume="1925" year="1925">Edwards 1925</bibRefCitation>
) from the British Isles, and the male hypopygium has been later illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="224255308BCE214F2CCB4B035285491A" author="Hutson, AM." journalOrPublisher="Handbooks for Identification of British Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Mycetophilidae (Bolitophilinae, Ditiomyiinae, Diadocidiinae, Keroplatinae, Sciophilinae and Manotinae). Diptera, Nematocera" year="1980">Hutson et al. 1980</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="F1BD90AF5C54EEE4214B9315C7977930" author="Zaitzev, A. I." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" title="Fungus gnats of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part 1." year="1994">Zaitzev 1994</bibRefCitation>
. The species has a European range, including Fennoscandia, northern Russia, Central Europe, Bulgaria and Hungary (
<bibRefCitation id="0760DCA6749A471AA1FD561359FF974B" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218">Chandler 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation id="F591AF5A3B5929A3C71FCDA54D8E9495" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
) described 
<taxonomicName id="455A7DA0899A9E8C730035270BCDEAD7" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
from the Chiba prefekture in Japan based on material collected from 
<taxonomicName id="A3881A3AF394F8F9BB093DF72E57B7BB" genus="Arisema" lsidName="Arisema serratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" rank="species" species="serratum">Arisema serratum</taxonomicName>
flowers. Sasakawa's description is very detailed, including illustrations on the male hypopygium, and hence we propose it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="E5F68F6E8F45EF4DE1371514629B806E" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
. In his discussion on 
<taxonomicName id="DAD45AB94C5D6E100EB66F711F9F733C" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
Sasakawa (
<bibRefCitation id="6513EDB945DCBD002E89D465B6D0BA47" author="Sasakawa, M." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" pagination="293 - 306" title="Fungus gnats associated with flowers of the genus Arisaema (Araceae). Part 2. Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera)" volume="20" year="1994">Sasakawa 1994</bibRefCitation>
, p. 300) does not mention 
<taxonomicName id="22203BC4D65EBDA8286A4F9B58AC7774" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
; instead, he compares his new species to rather distant species 
<taxonomicName id="24F79C407D0DD5371C79B676AEA1D283" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. nitida" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="nitida">B. nitida</taxonomicName>
Grzegorzek and 
<taxonomicName id="B5F4CE04EAC70480C05ECD7232128855" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. dispecta" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="dispecta">B. dispecta</taxonomicName>
Dziedzicki. It is likely that Sasakawa was not aware of 
<taxonomicName id="AB0DCF15C6CF4D07F5BC18C8E722C729" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. pallidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="pallidula">B. pallidula</taxonomicName>
while describing 
<taxonomicName id="157B578888A2C48860EB1B372FC3C968" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Biddulphiaceae" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="B. subnitidula" order="Biddulphiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="7218" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="subnitidula">B. subnitidula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
